        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="668" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d668">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.93/7–2845: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hurley</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Babelsberg</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-28">July 28,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Please deliver as soon as possible the following message to Dr. Soong: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>I understand you were to communicate with Marshal Stalin by 30th or 31st
                            July. I think it important that before that date you communicate with
                            him here through Moscow requesting opportunity to return to Moscow and
                            continue discussions in hope of reaching agreement.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>[<hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
